abstract: >-
  Journey Map Thinking (JMT) is a deterministic, LLM-free navigation layer that
  interleaves five typed checkpoints into an existing agent pipeline to track an
  agent's journey position. This repository bundles the preprint working paper
  with the reference implementation. The work reports a software mechanism
  verified by two independent toolchains and a frozen-position anchor that
  returned a powered null against Claude Code's own /compact, and makes no claim
  of superiority over any existing system.
